A lone figure sits hunched at a cluttered workstation in a dimly lit, rain-streaked room, surrounded by towering stacks of dusty technical manuals and tangled cables. The scene is rendered in moody cyberpunk style with neon pink and cyan accents bleeding through grimy windows. The developer's holographic monitors display cascading lines of chaotic, spaghetti-like code visualized as glowing threads that twist and knot into impossible tangles. Behind them, a faded corporate logo flickers on a cracked wall screen. Empty coffee cups and energy drink cans form small pyramids. Through the window, massive corporate towers loom indifferently in the smog-filled cityscape. The atmosphere conveys isolation, neglect, and the quiet desperation of someone trying to build something meaningful while completely cut off from guidance or support. A small wilting plant on the desk serves as the only organic element in this cold technological prison.
